              "id": "v1_ctx_prompt_1",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Read the text carefully to do the activities.\n\nTrafficking in human beings for the purpose of organ removal and human organ trade are universally condemned. However, the buying and selling of organs continues despite efforts to limit the illegal nature of this practice. It has been estimated that approximately 10% of all transplants may occur unlawfully.\n\nDoctors and other health care professionals are well placed to play an important role in reducing the illegal organ trade, including trafficking in human beings for the purpose of organ removal. They have unique access to patients' information and are in a position to provide patients with critical information about the nature of the illegal trade. In addition, they can provide valuable information that might support the police and judiciary in investigating and accusing organ trafficking networks.\n\nGovernments throughout the world can do more in fighting organ trafficking phenomenon. They should not only support research into the nature and scope of this crime but also pass stringent laws to punish human organ traffickers.\n\nAdapted from National Library of Medicine, National Institutes of Health. Jan. 4th, 2016."
            }
          ]
        },
