              "id": "v2_ctx_prompt_1",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Read the text carefully to do the activities.\n\nAs one of the oldest sciences, astronomy is part of every culture's history and roots. It has and continues to revolutionize our thinking on a worldwide scale. It has been used to measure time, mark the seasons, and navigate the vast oceans.\n\nSeveral reports indicate that astronomy represents a unique perspective that extends our horizons and helps us discover the beauty and grandeur of the Universe and our place within it. On a more pressing level, astronomy helps us learn how to assure the survival of our species. For example, it is important to study the Sun's influence on Earth's climate and how it will affect weather, water levels, etc. In addition, mapping the movement of all the objects in our Solar System allows us to predict the potential threats to our planet from the outer space.\n\nOn a personal level, teaching astronomy to our youth is of great value. It has been proven that pupils who engage in astronomy-related educational activities at school are more likely to pursue careers in science and technology, and to keep up-to-date with scientific discoveries.\n\nAdapted from: http://www.asc.osu.edu"
            }
